WEBVTT

00:00.125 --> 00:01.834
[Adam] Previously
on What About Brian:

00:01.834 --> 00:04.542
- I've gone crazy, haven't I?
- No, you're not crazy.

00:04.542 --> 00:07.166
You don't know what it's like
to do this alone.

00:07.166 --> 00:10.166
Carrie is suffering
from a permanent hearing loss.

00:10.166 --> 00:12.834
- Marjorie isn't my ex.
- Don't even start, Brian.

00:12.834 --> 00:16.375
You broke up a wedding
and didn't say a word
to me about it.

00:16.375 --> 00:20.500
Maybe we could not
tell anyone else that
I'm back in town just yet.

00:21.959 --> 00:25.000
[Deena] I didn't have anything
to do with this, honey. I swear.

00:25.834 --> 00:28.166
[rock music plays]

00:34.500 --> 00:35.667
Isn't that Deena?

00:36.750 --> 00:39.333
Hey, guys, come on.

00:39.333 --> 00:43.291
- I knew that was her
the other night.
- You knew who was what?

00:43.291 --> 00:46.208
- The other night?
- I should've never
listened to Ivy.

00:46.208 --> 00:48.875
She said it was guilt,
my mind was playing tricks.

00:48.875 --> 00:51.709
OK, one of you needs
to tell us what's going on.

00:51.709 --> 00:56.875
That was Marjorie.
Marjorie's here.

01:06.333 --> 01:10.542
- She's so still.
- She is still. She's sleeping.

01:10.542 --> 01:12.417
Doesn't look like she's
breathing.

01:12.417 --> 01:14.875
She was fine
the first time you came in here.

01:14.875 --> 01:18.542
She was fine the
second time you came in here.

01:18.542 --> 01:21.000
She's fine now.
I know what I'm doing.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.250
She doesn't sound like
she's breathing either. Bella.

01:24.250 --> 01:27.709
If you want to help Bella,
try turning down
the air conditioner.

01:27.709 --> 01:30.083
It's far too cold
in this room for a newborn.

01:30.083 --> 01:31.542
[Nicole] Oh.

01:32.333 --> 01:35.208
Thank God. She's OK.

01:36.875 --> 01:39.583
[toy] Red square.
Yellow circle.

01:39.583 --> 01:42.792
- [Bella cries]
- [toy] Blue triangle.
Hee-hee-hee.

01:42.792 --> 01:45.041
- You know what? You're fired.
- What?

01:45.041 --> 01:48.291
Yeah, just go, OK? Just go.
I don't like your attitude.

01:48.291 --> 01:52.000
- Attitude?
I'm great with Bella.
- You're not great with me.

01:52.000 --> 01:54.458
So just go,
and I'll send you a check.

01:55.667 --> 01:58.083
[Bella still crying]

01:58.083 --> 02:04.083
[sighs] I just wanted
to see them when I was ready.
On my terms. Not like this.

02:04.083 --> 02:07.583
Not in some restaurant. Not when
they're on some double date.

02:07.583 --> 02:13.083
I know, honey. But sometimes,
things just happen for a reason.

02:13.083 --> 02:16.959
It doesn't exactly
look like they're hurrying
over here to say hello.

02:16.959 --> 02:20.458
- So how are they?
- It took a while, but, uh...

02:20.458 --> 02:22.417
I think they're doing good.

02:22.417 --> 02:24.625
They're both fine.
They've moved on.

02:24.625 --> 02:27.417
- That's good.
- They haven't moved "on" on.

02:27.417 --> 02:31.834
You know, Brian and Bridget
just started dating,

02:31.834 --> 02:35.625
and let's see, Heather,
we don't really know
what that's all about.

02:35.625 --> 02:38.792
Adam and Heather,
is that serious?

02:40.583 --> 02:44.458
Well, that waiter
is taking a while, huh?

02:44.458 --> 02:45.959
- Deen?
- Huh?

02:45.959 --> 02:49.125
- Deena?
- They're married, Marjorie.

02:49.125 --> 02:52.208
So I guess...

02:52.208 --> 02:55.667
- Yeah, it is kind of serious.
- [laughs]

03:04.458 --> 03:08.041
This is getting ridiculous.
Just get it over with
and go say hi.

03:08.041 --> 03:10.375
We're not going over.
We're eating dinner.

03:10.375 --> 03:13.166
And the conversation's
been scintillating so far.

03:13.166 --> 03:15.875
Should we just
get it over with?

03:17.667 --> 03:19.000
Fine.

03:21.667 --> 03:24.333
- Great double date so far, huh?
- Yeah, great!

03:26.792 --> 03:30.667
[sighs] Maybe one of us
should call her or e-mail.

03:30.667 --> 03:33.750
A text could be good.
You wanna text her?

03:33.750 --> 03:37.417
I don't want to do anything.
I just want to forget
this ever happened.

03:39.583 --> 03:41.291
[tires screeching]

03:42.875 --> 03:45.208
You need to slow down.
You're gonna kill us!

03:45.208 --> 03:48.166
- I have to pee.
- I'm gonna cut you some slack.

03:48.166 --> 03:51.041
Obviously, this Marjorie thing
is bothering you.

03:51.041 --> 03:55.125
There's really no reason
to be upset. I saw her,
and it's all good.

03:55.125 --> 03:57.750
If you mean incredibly awkward,
it was fantastic.

03:57.750 --> 04:01.333
I didn't feel anything.
It was like seeing
an old friend. Nothing more.

04:01.333 --> 04:04.709
- [car accelerates]
- [tires screech]

04:06.875 --> 04:10.542
I'm really happy for you,
and I really appreciate
what you're saying

04:10.542 --> 04:12.875
but I really have to go now.

04:25.083 --> 04:27.834
- Hey.
- Hey, where's the fire?

04:27.834 --> 04:30.875
- OK, go ahead.
Ask me how my night was.
- How was your night?

04:30.875 --> 04:35.208
We ran into, at the restaurant,
you are not going to believe
who's back.

04:35.208 --> 04:37.750
- Marjorie.
- Marjorie.

04:37.750 --> 04:40.625
- Well, you knew she was back?
- I just found out today.

04:40.625 --> 04:43.917
Deena and I saw her name
on this list because
of this situation with Carrie.

04:43.917 --> 04:48.375
- Wait, what situation
with Carrie?
- [sighs] It's not good, dude.

04:52.125 --> 04:55.583
- Talk to me.
- Carrie's deaf.

04:57.125 --> 04:58.959
She lost her hearing.

04:58.959 --> 05:04.333
I mean, she had it, right?
They tested her when she
was a baby, but somehow...

05:04.333 --> 05:06.250
She'll get it back, right?

05:06.250 --> 05:08.959
That's what we're
trying to figure out.
It doesn't look good.

05:08.959 --> 05:11.125
Is there anything
I can do to help?

05:11.125 --> 05:15.959
Come on. You just be who you
are, who you always are,
with us, with her.

05:15.959 --> 05:17.625
You know I will.

05:17.625 --> 05:22.625
And if you were cool
with Marjorie helping us out,
that would be huge.

05:22.625 --> 05:26.083
Dave, it's Carrie.
I'm OK with whatever you need.

05:26.083 --> 05:27.583
It's not gonna bother you?

05:27.583 --> 05:31.625
- Look, I'm over Marjorie.
- Yeah.

05:31.625 --> 05:34.667
I gotta tell you, man,
you look a little
sweaty and weird.

05:34.667 --> 05:36.458
That's Bridget's fault.

05:36.458 --> 05:38.250
She wasn't happy
to see Marjorie?

05:38.250 --> 05:40.333
She's fine with that.
It's her driving.

05:40.333 --> 05:42.166
- Notice how bad she drives?
- No.

05:42.166 --> 05:44.333
She cuts people off.
She doesn't signal.

05:44.333 --> 05:45.875
- Uh-oh.
- Uh-oh what?

05:45.875 --> 05:48.875
- How long have
you two been together?
- Six weeks.

05:48.875 --> 05:51.041
I know what you're gonna say,
I sabotage.

05:51.041 --> 05:54.208
That's 'cause you do. Lisa B.
slurped her cereal milk,

05:54.208 --> 05:57.792
Angie breathed too loud
while chewing,
Karen used your toothbrush.

05:57.792 --> 06:02.291
I don't do that anymore. The
little things don't bother me.

06:02.291 --> 06:06.291
Hey, honey, I forgot my
toothbrush. Do you mind
if I use yours?

06:22.333 --> 06:25.542
- Are you coming to bed soon?
- Yeah, after I finish this.

06:27.625 --> 06:30.291
Go to bed.
I'll be there in a second.

06:31.834 --> 06:36.625
- OK.
- [soft rock plays]

06:42.875 --> 06:45.709
♪ Will you like
to watch the sunrise? ♪

06:45.709 --> 06:48.959
