people I met on the way down ♪

07:32.959 --> 07:38.917
♪ Calling all friends and
people I don't even know ♪

07:38.917 --> 07:40.792
♪ Calling on high ♪

07:40.792 --> 07:45.625
♪ I want to believe
there's a way now ♪

07:45.625 --> 07:50.458
♪ I'm too tired to pretend
I don't want to be alone ♪

07:50.458 --> 07:53.125
♪ I'm calling all friends ♪♪

08:00.542 --> 08:03.166
- What's with the box?
- Just some work clothes.

08:03.166 --> 08:05.250
I thought I'd
give them to Jasheika.

08:05.250 --> 08:09.625
Hmm. Some people's honeymoon
clothes, your work clothes.

08:12.291 --> 08:16.750
So we gonna talk about it?
The elephant in the restaurant.
This Marjorie thing.

08:16.750 --> 08:20.125
Or we just gonna pretend
and never mention it.

08:20.125 --> 08:24.250
Everything is normal, you know?
Marjorie and I are over
and I've moved on.

08:24.250 --> 08:27.000
Really? Because you
came to bed at 2:00am,

08:27.000 --> 08:29.333
and the way you
acted at the restaurant...

08:29.333 --> 08:33.166
How am I supposed to act?
I run into my ex-fiancée
who left me at the altar.

08:33.166 --> 08:38.500
- I know. It was really awkward.
- No more
than your ex suing you.

08:38.500 --> 08:40.667
He's not my ex.
I already told you.

08:40.667 --> 08:44.834
Well, you better tell him.
Because this whole false
promises thing,

08:44.834 --> 08:47.750
he clearly seems to think
you had something going on.

08:47.750 --> 08:50.542
Well, we didn't.
He was a client.

08:53.750 --> 08:56.709
How 'bout I just get my running
shoes and we go for a run?

08:56.709 --> 09:01.458
Actually, I already
called Brian. He's gonna
train with me today.

09:01.458 --> 09:04.208
Yeah, OK.
You guys have a good time.

09:04.208 --> 09:06.709
Yeah. All right,
have a good day.

09:11.542 --> 09:13.667
[rock music plays]

09:13.667 --> 09:16.291
♪ And the fun we had
just hanging around ♪

09:16.291 --> 09:19.041
♪ Nowhere to be
It's all good to me ♪

09:19.041 --> 09:20.583
[exhales deeply]

09:23.458 --> 09:24.709
What's wrong?

09:24.709 --> 09:28.041
Nothing. I just didn't
get a lot of sleep last night.

09:28.041 --> 09:31.041
And I haven't run
more than a mile... ever.

09:31.041 --> 09:34.208
Except that one time, to get to
the church for your wedding.

09:34.208 --> 09:37.166
- Funny.
- Anyway...

09:37.166 --> 09:40.041
Can I assume last night
didn't go well?

09:40.041 --> 09:43.542
Last night, this morning.
With Marjorie in Minneapolis,

09:43.542 --> 09:45.583
she was just gone.
Now that she's back in LA,

09:45.583 --> 09:51.041
it's as if I could
just run into her again
and be totally blindsided.

09:51.041 --> 09:53.917
I mean, it's just
all out of my control.

09:53.917 --> 09:57.083
I don't know.
Whatever. I'm fine.

09:57.083 --> 09:59.792
Why didn't you get any sleep?
Bridget?

09:59.792 --> 10:03.583
You don't sleep with Bridget.
You occupy space
and avoid getting hit.

10:03.583 --> 10:07.125
It's like sleeping
while someone lobs
grenades into your bed.

10:07.125 --> 10:11.583
Wow! Is it that time
again already? Has it
really been six weeks?

10:11.583 --> 10:15.417
- What's that supposed to mean?
- Well, how long's it been?

10:15.417 --> 10:18.583
Six weeks. That has nothing
to do with it. I don't sabotage.

10:18.583 --> 10:21.250
Why would I? I actually
wanna be in a relationship.

10:21.250 --> 10:23.041
Brian, you're
afraid to commit.

10:23.041 --> 10:26.792
All right? And you'll
find any reason not to.
And you always find one.

10:26.792 --> 10:29.625
- I'm not that guy anymore.
- OK, all right, I believe you.

10:29.625 --> 10:31.709
- No, you don't.
- Yeah, come on!

10:31.709 --> 10:33.625
- Let's go for a jog.
- No, I'm done.

10:33.625 --> 10:35.458
I'm not training for a marathon.

10:35.458 --> 10:38.041
- Exactly.
And you wanna know why?
- Why?

10:38.041 --> 10:39.291
Fear of commitment.

10:45.792 --> 10:49.709
So Carrie's file indicates
that the cochlear implant
is a viable option

10:49.709 --> 10:53.417
for her given the limited
high-decibel range
that she does hear.

10:53.417 --> 10:55.291
That's the surgery
we read about.

10:55.291 --> 10:59.333
It's an electronic device
that's surgically implanted
into the inner ear,

10:59.333 --> 11:03.125
and then she's given
an external speech processor,
which they would put,

11:03.125 --> 11:06.291
behind the ear, or she can wear
it in a belt or on a pocket.

11:06.291 --> 11:09.166
She's one.
What belt? What pocket?

11:09.166 --> 11:11.500
She's gonna just take it off
and chew on it.

11:11.500 --> 11:14.500
OK, but the surgery
could restore her hearing.

11:14.500 --> 11:17.542
- At least partially.
That's the hope.
- Not a guarantee.

11:17.542 --> 11:18.959
Nothing's a guarantee.

11:18.959 --> 11:22.667
The biggest risk is if they did
the implant and it fails,

11:22.667 --> 11:25.333
any residual hearing
could be lost.

11:25.333 --> 11:28.709
- So it's all or nothing?
- I know that this sounds risky,

11:28.709 --> 11:31.625
but the upside
for Carrie is huge.

11:31.625 --> 11:33.834
When would she be
old enough for surgery?

11:33.834 --> 11:39.000
- Any time after 12 months.
- OK, she'll be one on Saturday.

11:39.000 --> 11:41.166
Maybe we should
just cancel her party.

11:41.166 --> 11:45.000
No. We should do the party.
We keep everything
as normal as possible.

11:45.000 --> 11:49.000
Well, she's old enough,
so she can have the surgery.

11:50.709 --> 11:55.542
We... have to decide that.
It would be up to us.

11:55.542 --> 11:59.500
What would you do, Marjorie?
If Carrie was your daughter?

11:59.500 --> 12:02.166
As a doctor, I can't really
answer that question.

12:02.166 --> 12:05.750
But you're not just a doctor.
You're our friend.

12:05.750 --> 12:08.542
This is Carrie
we're talking about.

12:08.542 --> 12:12.834
OK. If it were up to me,
I would do the surgery.

12:15.333 --> 12:19.000
OK. Then that's
what we should do.

12:27.333 --> 12:29.375
OK. What's the emergency?
Is Bella OK?

12:29.375 --> 12:33.208
I can't get this thing to work.
Since when did women
pump milk anyway?

12:33.208 --> 12:37.583
Yeah, I've really never seen
a contraption like this before.

12:37.583 --> 12:41.208
Except at the Pleasure Hut,
but I think that
was something different.

12:41.208 --> 12:44.959
Hiya. I'm Alexa,
Bella's nanny.

12:44.959 --> 12:46.583
Hiya, how are you?

12:47.417 --> 12:49.250
Brian, focus.

12:49.250 --> 12:52.583
On your boobs? Doesn't that
fall under Alexa's jurisdiction?

12:52.583 --> 12:54.041
I don't think so.

12:54.041 --> 12:57.083
There's a bottle in the fridge.
Could you get it for me?

12:57.083 --> 13:00.917
Sure. But, I'm not all that
comfortable giving it to her.

13:00.917 --> 13:04.333
- Newborns kind of freak me out.
- [Bella fussing]

13:04.333 --> 13:06.917
Here, here. Oh.

13:07.709 --> 13:09.375
Hey.

13:11.417 --> 13:14.834
You need to fire that girl.
She's too hot to be a nanny
and too dumb.

13:14.834 --> 13:18.875
How's my baby girl? Who's the
cutest baby in the world?

13:18.875 --> 13:23.917
It's not that easy.
It's like going on one bad
blind date after another.

13:23.917 --> 13:26.917
- She can't even
find the bottle!
- Should I go help her?

13:26.917 --> 13:30.291
No. You gotta tell me
what happened last night.

13:30.291 --> 13:34.166
- The worst double date?
- I can't believe
Marjorie's back.

13:34.166 --> 13:36.792
What are the odds of you
and Adam running into her?

13:36.792 --> 13:38.333
And Heather and Bridget.

13:38.333 --> 13:41.500
- Why do I always
miss the good stuff?
- You didn't miss much.

13:41.500 --> 13:45.792
We didn't even talk.
But still, it was like
everything came rushing back.

13:45.792 --> 13:49.625
If you tell me you
have feelings for Marjorie,
I'll attach this pump...

13:49.625 --> 13:52.291
I only felt guilt for
everything I put her through.

13:52.291 --> 13:56.834
Maybe you should apologize
to Marjorie. So you can
move forward with Bridget.

13:56.834 --> 13:59.250
How long has it been anyway?
A month?

14:01.041 --> 14:02.834
It's been six weeks, OK?

14:02.834 --> 14:05.166
Don't pretend you don't know.
Everyone knows.

14:05.166 --> 14:07.583
- [Bella fussing]
- I'm not gonna sabotage!

14:07.583 --> 14:10.834
- Someone's a little sensitive.
- I gotta go.

14:12.875 --> 14:15.083
- What? I don't get a kiss?
- No.

14:16.417 --> 14:18.959
I don't get a kiss.
I don't get a kiss.

14:18.959 --> 14:22.166
Summer and I,
we had a real relationship.

14:22.166 --> 14:27.041
- That's not even her real name.
- I know. It's Heather.

14:27.041 --> 14:32.333
But she'll always
be Summer to me. We were
meant to be together, OK?

14:32.333 --> 14:34.667
She knows it as well as I do.

14:36.875 --> 14:39.208
- What's this?
- Proof.

14:39.208 --> 14:41.917
Receipts. For everything
that I bought her.

14:41.917 --> 14:47.208
A car, the ring, flat-screen,
trip home to see her mother,

14:47.208 --> 14:49.875
and I was gonna buy her
a boob job, but, well...

14:49.875 --> 14:55.500
- ...she met you first.
- This doesn't prove anything.

14:55.500 --> 14:58.291
Except that you
like to throw money away.

14:58.291 --> 15:00.000
OK.

15:01.625 --> 15:04.125
Well, then, maybe this does.

15:06.625 --> 15:08.208
[scoffs]

15:08.959 --> 15:11.375
Heather and I?

15:11.375 --> 15:13.875
We had an arrangement.
A sort of deal.

15:13.875 --> 15:16.375
Heather wouldn't
make "a sort of deal."

15:24.792 --> 15:28.208
I guess you don't know your wife
as well as you thought, huh?

15:30.250 --> 15:32.375
We should pack
and get out of here.

15:32.375 --> 15:34.041
Thank God we brought
separate cars.

15:34.041 --> 15:37.166
Could you give me a five-minute
head start for my own safety?

15:37.166 --> 15:40.250
Why are you obsessing about
my driving? It's getting mean.

15:40.250 --> 15:42.917
So I have one
less-than-perfect quality.
So what?

15:42.917 --> 15:46.291
One? Stealing the covers
and always talking
on your phone?

15:46.291 --> 15:48.375
I always have
to be available for work.

15:48.375 --> 15:52.417
- While we're having sex?
- I left my Bluetooth
in one time.

15:52.417 --> 15:56.375
How many times can you watch
the same episode
of SportsCenter?

15:56.375 --> 15:58.417
You send chain emails.

15:58.417 --> 16:00.750
I hate when you sing
in that stupid voice.

16:00.750 --> 16:04.834
And that code name
that you guys have for
hot girls? "Hey, Jimmy!"

16:04.834 --> 16:07.458
It's not as annoying
as when you talk on the phone.

16:07.458 --> 16:10.792
Oh, I'm sorry, I meant scream.
It's not a ship-to-shore call!

16:10.792 --> 16:14.291
- It's 2007.
Talk in a normal voice!
- [gasps]

16:22.458 --> 16:26.792
Wow, um...
that probably sounded...

16:26.792 --> 16:28.583
...ridiculous. I'm sorry.

16:29.625 --> 16:31.667
I think that was our first
couple fight.

16:31.667 --> 16:34.375
- I think so.
- Yeah.

16:36.291 --> 16:40.667
- So, what do we do now?
- I can think of a few ideas.

16:41.667 --> 16:44.667
- Hey, Jimmy.
- [both chuckle]

16:44.667 --> 16:46.917
No, hot girl. Right here.

16:46.917 --> 16:49.542
Oh, so,
what do you have in mind?

16:49.542 --> 16:52.333
First fight,
first makeup sex.

16:52.333 --> 16:54.500
Sounds good to me.

16:54.500 --> 16:57.333
But I have to
go somewhere right now.

16:57.333 --> 16:59.125
Can we have makeup sex
when I'm done?

16:59.125 --> 17:00.834
Yeah. Where do you
have to go?

17:00.834 --> 17:03.959
I don't want to lie to you,
but I don't want you
to freak out.

17:03.959 --> 17:06.625
I called Marjorie.
I just want to talk to her.

17:06.625 --> 17:11.000
- Why?
- We're just...
we're having coffee today.

17:11.000 --> 17:14.500
I just want to see her
so I can apologize
for everything.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.500
If I stopped your wedding,
I'd do the same.

17:16.500 --> 17:18.417
- Comforting.
- You know what I mean.

17:18.417 --> 17:21.625
You picked a fight
with me so you can
have coffee with Marjorie

17:21.625 --> 17:23.917
- without feeling guilty.
- Of course not.

17:23.917 --> 17:27.083
- Well, guess what? Now you can.
- Bridget, come on.

17:27.083 --> 17:31.667
I'm just gonna go run
some red lights and talk
on my cell phone real loud.

17:31.667 --> 17:33.667
You have fun with Marjorie.

17:34.917 --> 17:37.125
[tires screech]

17:42.917 --> 17:44.834
[Marjorie] Brian.

17:44.834 --> 17:46.375
- Hey.
- Hi.

17:47.667 --> 17:50.834
- You look great.
- You too.

17:50.834 --> 17:55.125
- Large americano, right?
- Yeah.

17:55.125 --> 17:59.583
So... what's new?
Are you back for good?

17:59.583 --> 18:03.041
I think so. I got offered
a position at Cedars.

18:03.041 --> 18:06.125
And I found a cute place
for rent up Beachwood Canyon.

18:06.125 --> 18:09.250
Beachwood,
that's a great place to buy.

18:09.250 --> 18:11.375
Oh, that's right.

18:11.375 --> 18:16.083
Deena told me you're some
hotshot real estate agent.
You and your girlfriend?

18:16.083 --> 18:19.959
Yeah, my girlfriend. We'll see
how much longer that lasts.

18:19.959 --> 18:22.709
- You wanna talk about it?
- It seems inappropriate.

18:22.709 --> 18:25.583
I didn't want to meet
so we could talk
about my problems.

18:25.583 --> 18:30.583
Well, we used to talk about it,
you know, all the time, before.

18:30.583 --> 18:32.583
Before I ruined everything.

18:33.750 --> 18:36.375
- I think I did that.
- No.

18:36.375 --> 18:40.083
I think every day how I wish
I could've kept my mouth shut.

18:40.083 --> 18:44.458
Stopping your wedding?
I was so selfish
and completely out of line.

18:44.458 --> 18:49.500
The reason you left Adam,
left LA, left...
your life was because of me.

18:49.500 --> 18:50.959
I'm just...

18:53.500 --> 18:54.792
...so sorry.

18:54.792 --> 18:58.125
Brian, leaving the church
that day, leaving LA,

18:58.125 --> 19:00.083
that was my decision.

19:00.083 --> 19:04.625
Whatever we did wrong,
whatever feelings
were there between us,

19:04.625 --> 19:08.125
I think they were there
because I was afraid
of getting married.

19:08.125 --> 19:10.417
I felt cornered, I ran.

19:10.417 --> 19:15.834
I wish that I would
have gone through with it
and know what I wanted.

19:15.834 --> 19:20.000
Then I'd be
married to Adam...

19:20.000 --> 19:25.375
...and I could be sitting here
with you talking about your
girlfriend troubles.

19:25.375 --> 19:29.166
I miss that, you know?
I miss being your friend.

19:30.959 --> 19:35.458
It's not... troubles, really.
It's kind of good, actually.

19:35.458 --> 19:40.458
We just got in a fight
before I came over here,
because I...

19:40.458 --> 19:44.917
[sighs] I started listing
her annoying qualities.

19:46.959 --> 19:48.667
That's not
always a good idea.

19:48.667 --> 19:51.125
Yeah, then she listed
my annoying qualities,

19:51.125 --> 19:54.458
and I told her I was
meeting you to talk
and then next thing I know,

19:54.458 --> 19:58.333
- she just took off.
- Six weeks, huh?

19:58.333 --> 20:03.125
- Apparently, this is what I do.
- So don't do it anymore,
you know?

20:03.125 --> 20:06.500
Maybe the six-week rule
doesn't even exist.

20:06.500 --> 20:10.041
If you really like this girl,
don't do what you did with me.

20:10.041 --> 20:11.875
Don't wait
until it's too late.

20:17.625 --> 20:19.041
I'm glad you're back.

20:20.208 --> 20:21.875
Me too.

20:25.667 --> 20:27.875
Here.

20:27.875 --> 20:30.041
No, I thought
I would just sit with her...

20:30.041 --> 20:31.875
You need sleep.

20:31.875 --> 20:34.208
Yeah, but I also need...

20:35.709 --> 20:39.041
You know, I have a vat
of Chunky Monkey in the freezer.

20:39.041 --> 20:40.709
I don't eat monkey.

20:41.875 --> 20:44.709
Well, we could just talk.

20:45.709 --> 20:48.542
I talk to baby.
Not to mama.

20:53.917 --> 20:56.250
You know, this just
isn't working out.

21:01.750 --> 21:05.583
Hey, you're home.
I've been keeping dinner warm.
Spaghetti carbonara.

21:05.583 --> 21:07.750
Thanks.
I already ate with Jimmy.

21:07.750 --> 21:10.709
Um, you don't
want anything at all?

21:10.709 --> 21:12.917
No, thanks.

21:14.625 --> 21:16.166
Is something the matter?

21:16.166 --> 21:18.500
I don't think
I can represent you, Heather.

21:18.500 --> 21:20.417
What do you mean? Why not?

21:20.417 --> 21:24.375
Well, I had a meeting
with Schmitty and his lawyer.

21:24.375 --> 21:28.083
He showed me all
the receipts and the pictures
of you and him together.

21:29.125 --> 21:32.125
- So?
- So it's obvious what this is.

21:32.125 --> 21:35.709
He bought you stuff,
he took care of you
in exchange for... for what?

21:35.709 --> 21:37.750
I'm guessing more
than lap dances.

21:37.750 --> 21:40.208
- Adam, he was a client.
- I have clients too.

21:40.208 --> 21:43.458
I don't buy them presents
or take them
for all-night sessions

21:43.458 --> 21:45.000
in the eternity room.

21:46.333 --> 21:49.125
What you're doing,
it's so textbook,
it's ridiculous.

21:49.125 --> 21:52.083
You're upset about Marjorie
so you're picking a fight.

21:52.083 --> 21:54.834
So in addition to being
a stripper and chiropractor,

21:54.834 --> 21:56.125
you're a therapist too.

21:56.125 --> 21:58.959
Sorry I'm not a squeaky-clean
doctor like Marjorie.

21:58.959 --> 22:02.250
- Leave Marjorie out of this.
- Why? You obviously can't.

22:02.250 --> 22:04.959
I don't understand
why you have her
on this pedestal

22:04.959 --> 22:09.291
after the way she treated you.
I'm the one who married you,
not her.

22:09.291 --> 22:12.291
- I'm the one
who's being honest.
- Well, then be honest.

22:12.291 --> 22:15.166
And tell me the truth.
Did you sleep with him or not?

22:16.583 --> 22:20.625
Does it even matter?
Would you even believe
anything I said?

22:22.500 --> 22:24.667
[phone rings]

22:28.375 --> 22:31.542
- Hey.
- I've been doing some research
on the Internet

22:31.542 --> 22:33.542
about this
cochlear thing.

22:33.542 --> 22:36.458
And a lot of deaf people
are against it.

22:36.458 --> 22:40.125
You know that?
If deaf people are against it,
that says something.

22:40.125 --> 22:43.500
It just might.
I'm here at the hospital,
actually. I could ask.

22:43.500 --> 22:45.834
- Is Carrie all right?
- Carrie is fine.

22:45.834 --> 22:49.125
- I left you a message.
- I'm not at work.
What's the message?

22:49.125 --> 22:52.500
I'm here with Marjorie.
She got us in to meet
with a surgeon.

22:52.500 --> 22:55.208
Wait. Are you making
decisions without me?

22:55.208 --> 22:58.041
- We haven't decided anything.
- We? You and Marjorie?

22:58.041 --> 23:02.291
Dave, listen, please don't
get mad. I left you a message,

23:02.291 --> 23:04.667
I had an opportunity, I took it.

23:04.667 --> 23:07.834
Nobody's gonna be deciding
anything without you,
I promise.

23:07.834 --> 23:09.709
[door opens]

23:09.709 --> 23:11.750
[man] Sorry
to keep you waiting.

23:11.750 --> 23:13.750
Dr. Baron.
Thank you for seeing us.

23:13.750 --> 23:17.166
- Dave, I have to go now, OK?
- No, you don't gotta go.
Deena! Deena!

23:17.166 --> 23:18.917
[phone beeps off]

23:18.917 --> 23:21.333
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

23:27.208 --> 23:30.166
- [knocking]
- Come in.

23:32.709 --> 23:33.875
[Adam clears throat]

23:33.875 --> 23:36.208
- Hi.
- Hi.

23:37.583 --> 23:41.208
Uh... I don't
have an appointment.

23:42.875 --> 23:44.458
That, and I'm not six.

23:44.458 --> 23:47.583
That's OK.
What're you doing here?

23:47.583 --> 23:51.375
Not that I mind
that you're here.
I'm glad you're here. I just...

23:51.375 --> 23:52.917
Please, stop me.

23:52.917 --> 23:56.125
Yeah. I just thought
we could get this whole

23:56.125 --> 23:59.458
seeing-each-other-for-the-first
-time thing over with.

23:59.458 --> 24:03.250
Technically,
it's the second time.
The first time was other night.

24:04.583 --> 24:08.917
Right. But you left
before I could say anything.

24:11.083 --> 24:12.583
What did you want to say?

24:12.583 --> 24:16.208
I just wanted
to say that I'm fine.

24:16.208 --> 24:19.125
You know, that I'm happy.
I've moved on.

24:19.125 --> 24:21.458
- I heard.
- What's what supposed to mean?

24:21.458 --> 24:24.667
I talked to Deena.
She said that you're married.

24:24.667 --> 24:27.000
Pretty much
the definition of "moved on."

24:27.000 --> 24:28.375
You have
a problem with that?

24:28.375 --> 24:33.959
We were supposed to spend
the rest of our lives together,

24:33.959 --> 24:37.875
and then you go off a month
later and marry some other girl.

24:39.959 --> 24:43.792
It's like, well,
if this one doesn't work,
you just plug in this one?

24:44.542 --> 24:46.333
No, it wasn't like that.

24:46.333 --> 24:49.667
I was gone for three months,
and you fell in love with
somebody else.

24:49.667 --> 24:51.959
You're in no position
to give me grief.

24:51.959 --> 24:54.625
I'm not trying
to give you grief. Who is she?

24:54.625 --> 24:58.250
She's a girl that I met
the night of our bachelor party.

24:58.250 --> 25:01.792
- The night before our wedding?
- The night you went to Brian's.

25:01.792 --> 25:05.583
We had the rehearsal dinner
then the guys took you
to that strip club.

25:11.792 --> 25:15.041
That's where you met her?
You married a stripper?

25:15.041 --> 25:20.000
- She doesn't do that anymore.
- What're you doing?
This isn't you.

25:20.000 --> 25:22.709
You know what? How do
you know what's me anymore?

25:22.709 --> 25:27.500
You didn't stick around
to find out. You don't
get to know what I'm doing,

25:27.500 --> 25:32.500
or who I'm with. You gave up
that right when you left.

25:32.500 --> 25:35.625
All you need to know about my
life is you're not a part of it.

25:35.625 --> 25:40.166
You know, I'm really
glad we got this talk
over with, because...

25:40.166 --> 25:43.709
...maybe it won't be
so awkward next time
we run into each other.

25:51.375 --> 25:55.542
I'm so sorry. I feel
like this is all my fault.
I shouldn't have called you.

25:55.542 --> 25:58.500
Oh, no, no, no. I'm really glad
that you called, OK?

25:58.500 --> 26:02.542
This is the one place
I feel where I can
actually do some good.

26:02.542 --> 26:05.834
- Hey. Hey, Marjorie.
- Hi.

26:05.834 --> 26:09.709
- What's going on?
- I thought we could talk
about what happened today.

26:09.709 --> 26:12.041
Listen, the hospital thing
was my fault.

26:12.041 --> 26:15.625
We thought if you
heard another opinion,
you might feel better.

26:15.625 --> 26:19.875
I get it, but what I don't get
is why is Marjorie suddenly
your partner in this

26:19.875 --> 26:22.625
instead of me?
OK, Carrie's my daughter.

26:22.625 --> 26:24.417
No one's leaving
you out, Dave.

26:24.417 --> 26:27.583
I pulled some strings because
the surgeon was in town.

26:27.583 --> 26:30.375
Could you stay out of this?
It's between me and Deena.

26:30.375 --> 26:31.750
- Yeah, I should go.
- OK.

26:31.750 --> 26:34.250
No, Marjorie, don't go.

26:34.250 --> 26:37.667
You blew through here
like a hurricane
and destroyed everything.

26:37.667 --> 26:42.375
And now you wanna be friends.
This is my daughter's health
we're talking about.

26:42.375 --> 26:45.083
- We should get
a neutral doctor.
- Dave!

26:45.083 --> 26:48.750
A doctor's who's not gonna
take your side over my side!

26:48.750 --> 26:51.917
- I'm gonna go.
- [girls] Daddy's here!

26:51.917 --> 26:56.417
Hey! Pumpkins.
How are you, my sweet?

26:56.417 --> 26:58.333
Get some dinner,
get some dinner.

27:01.041 --> 27:05.667
Listen, Dave.
There are no sides here.

27:05.667 --> 27:08.542
She was getting us help
no other doctor could get us.

27:08.542 --> 27:10.792
Getting us in to see
the best surgeon in town

27:10.792 --> 27:15.458
precisely because she
is our friend.
You should be thanking her.

27:15.458 --> 27:16.959
I know. It's just...

27:16.959 --> 27:22.291
She made a mistake,
with the boys back then.
I've made them.

27:22.291 --> 27:23.792
God knows, we both have.

27:28.750 --> 27:31.125
Marjorie!
Hold on a second please!

27:31.125 --> 27:34.959
- Dave, please, it's a big city.
- We don't have
to see one another.

27:34.959 --> 27:39.291
Don't be ridiculous.
I don't want you to do that.
I was totally out of line.

27:39.291 --> 27:41.500
- No, you weren't.
- Yeah, I was.

27:41.500 --> 27:44.291
I took everything out on you
and I shouldn't have.

27:44.291 --> 27:48.500
These last few months
have been really hard for me.
The worst of my life.

27:48.500 --> 27:50.333
And this thing with Carrie,

27:50.333 --> 27:54.834
you'd think it'd make us
put our petty problems in
perspective, but it hasn't.

27:54.834 --> 27:57.166
You and Deena
are gonna work through this.

27:57.166 --> 28:01.792
I don't know.
I just don't wanna feel like
I'm going through this alone.

28:01.792 --> 28:07.125
It's hard being alone.
But you're not.
You know, I promise.

28:09.458 --> 28:11.709
Come to Carrie's
birthday party tomorrow.

28:11.709 --> 28:13.875
That's OK.
You don't have to do that.

28:13.875 --> 28:18.166
I know I don't have to, but you
belong there as much as anyone.

28:18.166 --> 28:21.458
We want you there.
I want you there.

28:27.208 --> 28:30.542
Stupid beach parking. Look,
that guy's taking up two spots.

28:30.542 --> 28:34.208
What's wrong with people?
OK, what's this guy doing?

28:34.208 --> 28:37.500
- Look at him. Come on!
- [honks horn]

28:39.000 --> 28:40.542
- [tires screech]
- [scoffs]

28:40.542 --> 28:43.250
I'm sorry.

28:43.250 --> 28:47.500
I'm really glad
you decided to come.

28:47.500 --> 28:51.834
Yeah, I'm glad you called.
Ooh! There's one!

28:51.834 --> 28:53.875
I want things
to be good with us.

28:53.875 --> 28:57.333
The whole reason I went to see
Marjorie was for you and me.

28:57.333 --> 29:01.083
It's because I want to, you
know, move things forward.

29:01.083 --> 29:04.375
I wanna take things to the next
level. And I was thinking,

29:04.375 --> 29:07.834
maybe you'd want
to move in.

29:07.834 --> 29:11.583
With me. And technically,
Dave, four days a week.

29:11.583 --> 29:12.667
But mostly me.

29:19.000 --> 29:20.709
[exhales]

29:26.709 --> 29:31.041
Are you mad at me? I asked you
to move in. A normal person
would be touched.

29:31.041 --> 29:35.125
A normal person doesn't ask
somebody to move in after
knowing them for what?

29:35.125 --> 29:37.750
Six weeks. We've known
each other for six weeks.

29:37.750 --> 29:40.667
Yeah, and my point is that
normal people don't do that

29:40.667 --> 29:42.917
unless they're trying
to overcompensate.

29:42.917 --> 29:46.583
You go and see Marjorie,
now you're asking me
to move in with you.

29:46.583 --> 29:49.750
- It's pretty clear
what's going on.
- Well, to you, maybe.

29:49.750 --> 29:53.667
It's a sweet gesture,
but you're just trying
to prove you're over her.

29:53.667 --> 29:56.792
I am trying to prove that.
To you.

29:56.792 --> 29:58.417
Yeah, way too hard.

29:58.417 --> 30:02.208
Bridget, why can't you
believe this has nothing
to do with Marjorie

30:02.208 --> 30:03.959
and everything
to do with you?

30:03.959 --> 30:05.583
[horn honks]

30:05.583 --> 30:06.834
[soft rock plays]

30:06.834 --> 30:08.125
♪ I suddenly realized ♪

30:08.125 --> 30:11.709
♪ We're all in this together ♪

30:11.709 --> 30:14.291
Wait. Bridget.

30:14.291 --> 30:17.125
I'm tired of busting my butt.
I wanna make partner.

30:17.125 --> 30:20.125
- To the 405 to the ten.
- And get off on Lincoln?

30:20.125 --> 30:23.125
No... you can forget the ten
and just take Venice.

30:23.125 --> 30:26.250
Or you can take the 110
from downtown and...

30:26.250 --> 30:29.959
- ...right?
- I don't know.

30:29.959 --> 30:32.542
- Hey.
- Hi. Let's get a drink.

30:32.542 --> 30:34.542
They have drinks
at this thing, right?

30:34.542 --> 30:37.208
I think I saw a
juice box somewhere.

30:37.208 --> 30:41.291
Man, pigs in a blanket
are going fast.
Or is it pig in a blankets?

30:41.291 --> 30:44.000
- Pigs.
- Pigs, oh.

30:46.959 --> 30:49.667
- How're you doing, honey?
- Oh, you know, not well.

30:49.667 --> 30:52.583
You're doing everything you can
to take care of Carrie,

30:52.583 --> 30:54.458
to take care of everything.

30:54.458 --> 30:57.500
Doing this mom thing
on your own, it's really hard.

30:57.500 --> 30:59.917
Well, the only thing worse
than doing it alone

30:59.917 --> 31:02.542
is having another person there
and feeling alone.

31:02.542 --> 31:05.291
I know, I fired three nannies
for the same reason.

31:05.291 --> 31:08.000
Oh, my gosh! No, I have
the perfect nanny for you.

31:08.000 --> 31:11.959
- Oh, no,
I think I'm done with nannies.
- No, listen.

31:11.959 --> 31:15.875
You call this agency,
tell them you want
an interview with Jamie.

31:17.667 --> 31:19.458
Just call. Trust me.

31:22.542 --> 31:24.125
- So...
- So...

31:25.834 --> 31:28.875
I keep forgetting. You all know
each other from the firm.

31:28.875 --> 31:32.709
- Yes! And the wedding.
- Mmm.

31:32.709 --> 31:37.792
God, you know what
was the worst?
Those firm cocktail parties.

31:37.792 --> 31:42.000
With that pervy guy, Fletcher.
Did he ever used to try
to cop a feel?

31:42.000 --> 31:43.875
Yes!

31:47.917 --> 31:51.333
This has got to be one
of the worst one-year-old
birthday parties.

31:55.500 --> 31:59.083
- Hey.
- Want some?

31:59.083 --> 32:00.250
No, thanks.

32:06.000 --> 32:08.583
- It's OK for this to be hard,
you know?
- I know.

32:08.583 --> 32:13.083
I always knew I
was second choice.
I just never felt it until now.

32:14.792 --> 32:17.375
- What am I supposed to do?
- Oh, no, no.

32:17.375 --> 32:21.000
No, don't ask me.
I am not the expert.

32:21.000 --> 32:24.208
I convinced my husband
to sleep with another woman

32:24.208 --> 32:25.917
so I could sleep
with another man.

32:25.917 --> 32:28.208
And we didn't
notice our daughter

32:28.208 --> 32:30.250
had a very serious
medical condition,

32:30.250 --> 32:32.250
and now we can't
decide what to do.

32:32.250 --> 32:35.417
We can't even agree
on vanilla or chocolate.

32:35.417 --> 32:39.166
- You know what?
I will have a glass.
- OK.

32:43.125 --> 32:45.250
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

32:48.625 --> 32:52.250
This is what you have
to look forward to.
Kids' birthday parties.

32:52.250 --> 32:54.500
Yeah, well, I think
at the rate I'm going,

32:54.500 --> 32:58.208
I'm not gonna have to worry
about that anytime soon.

32:58.208 --> 33:02.625
I thought things were getting
serious with you and Brian.

33:02.625 --> 33:08.125
I heard he asked you to move in.
I know this is none
of my business.

33:08.125 --> 33:13.959
Well, I do know my brother.
And for what it's worth,
asking you to move in,

33:13.959 --> 33:18.625
that's about the biggest
commitment that
he's ever made... ever.

33:18.625 --> 33:23.333
I mean, no woman has seen
the inside of that apartment
for more than 48 hours.

33:25.291 --> 33:26.959
Not even her.

33:26.959 --> 33:31.625
So you must...
really mean something to him.

33:32.834 --> 33:34.125
Thank you.

33:36.792 --> 33:38.291
[sighs]

33:38.291 --> 33:41.792
- Hey, need some help?
- I forgot the candles.

33:43.166 --> 33:45.333
All I need is one stupid candle.

33:45.333 --> 33:47.834
I can't find a candle because
I always think I have them

33:47.834 --> 33:50.542
and then I... [sighs]

33:50.542 --> 33:52.792
We put them in there
on Larissa's birthday

33:52.792 --> 33:55.125
because we always
forget the candles.

33:57.792 --> 34:01.500
- You're just so...
- Great, I know.

34:04.250 --> 34:08.959
- I need you.
- You have me, anytime.

34:10.875 --> 34:11.875
[exhales]

34:12.542 --> 34:14.000
- OK.
- Ready?

34:14.000 --> 34:17.000
- A little birthday cheer?
- Yes.

34:17.000 --> 34:21.291
- All right.
- [Brian] Here comes
the birthday girl.

34:21.291 --> 34:25.542
[all singing]
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

34:25.542 --> 34:30.041
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

34:30.041 --> 34:33.375
[sound fades]

35:03.291 --> 35:04.917
Heather!

35:07.583 --> 35:09.083
Great.

35:10.917 --> 35:16.709
- You OK?
- Yeah, I don't know
what I am anymore.

35:16.709 --> 35:18.542
I'm sure you guys
will work it out.

35:21.667 --> 35:25.959
This, coming from my ex-fiancée.
That's... sweet.

35:25.959 --> 35:28.667
- We should probably go inside.
- Yeah, yeah.

35:28.667 --> 35:30.834
I think I'm actually
just gonna take off.

35:30.834 --> 35:32.166
OK.

35:32.166 --> 35:35.125
Uh... um...

35:37.959 --> 35:39.709
Do you wanna come with me?

35:43.000 --> 35:45.125
- Sure.
- All right.

35:55.583 --> 35:59.291
She seems nice. Heather.

35:59.291 --> 36:01.125
Yeah. She's a good girl.

36:02.917 --> 36:06.625
It was fun being
with everyone again.

36:06.625 --> 36:11.667
[Marjorie sighs] You forget
how much you miss everything.

36:17.500 --> 36:19.000
A lot's changed.

36:21.083 --> 36:24.667
Last year feels
like a lifetime ago.

36:24.667 --> 36:30.166
This is nice. I was worried
that we'd never get back here.

36:30.166 --> 36:34.625
I forgot how easy it is
to be with you. I miss that.

36:36.834 --> 36:39.500
- Me too.
- Hey, don't cry.

36:39.500 --> 36:44.709
- [sobbing] I'm sorry, Adam.
- Hey.

36:48.083 --> 36:54.083
Would you be honest with me?
Are you happy? I mean, really?

36:54.083 --> 36:58.542
- Adam...
- What does it matter what I am?

36:59.500 --> 37:01.625
This is my life now.

37:03.333 --> 37:06.041
It matters if you still
have feelings for me.

37:06.041 --> 37:08.375
What do you want me to say,
Marjorie?

37:08.375 --> 37:13.709
Of course, I have feelings
for you. I wanted to marry you.

37:13.709 --> 37:16.792
We should be spending our
lives together, but we're not,

37:16.792 --> 37:18.709
because things
are the way they are.

37:20.000 --> 37:22.041
The past is the past.

37:22.041 --> 37:26.208
Leaving you was the biggest
mistake of my life.

37:26.208 --> 37:30.333
And I thought about you
every day that I was gone.

37:31.000 --> 37:32.500
I just...

37:34.291 --> 37:36.834
I just... I want you back.

37:38.000 --> 37:40.583
I wanna forget about the past.
I want a future.

37:43.709 --> 37:45.834
I want our future.

37:49.709 --> 37:52.709
[soft music plays]

37:52.709 --> 37:55.542
♪ But I'm feeling misled ♪

37:55.542 --> 37:59.583
♪ And I don't know
how much I believe ♪

37:59.583 --> 38:03.083
- Wait, wait, wait!
- I gotta go.

38:03.083 --> 38:06.083
♪ My head aches ♪

38:06.083 --> 38:09.583
♪ Love takes me ♪

38:09.583 --> 38:12.917
♪ Deep underground ♪

38:12.917 --> 38:14.667
- Mike, hey.
- Hey.

38:14.667 --> 38:18.917
- Is Vincent around?
- In the back office, I think.

38:18.917 --> 38:22.709
Hey, you coming back
to work here? Things
aren't the same without you.

38:22.709 --> 38:25.750
- I don't know.
I'm thinking about it.
- Good.

38:27.792 --> 38:29.750
- Thanks.
- Don't thank me.

38:29.750 --> 38:32.834
It's on Schmitty.

38:32.834 --> 38:38.583
♪ In my defense
There is no evidence ♪

38:38.583 --> 38:44.250
♪ Putting me at the scene
of the crime ♪

38:44.250 --> 38:47.583
- Is this some kind
of a peace offering?
- Maybe.

38:47.583 --> 38:51.083
Then we should probably talk
and straighten this mess out.

38:51.083 --> 38:52.709
I'm sitting right here.

38:55.166 --> 38:59.375
Mike, two more.

38:59.375 --> 39:02.208
♪ The earth quakes ♪

39:02.208 --> 39:05.500
♪ And my heart awakes ♪

39:07.166 --> 39:10.208
- Nice signaling.
- [Bridget laughs]

39:10.208 --> 39:12.625
I try.

39:12.625 --> 39:16.125
So I guess it did sound a little
crazy, asking you to move in.

39:16.125 --> 39:20.875
Well, that's funny because it's
starting to sound better to me.

39:20.875 --> 39:24.500
Wait, are you serious?

39:24.500 --> 39:29.542
Yeah, I think so. I mean,
if you think you're OK with it.

39:29.542 --> 39:32.375
You, me and Dave under one roof?
It's perfect.

39:32.375 --> 39:35.625
Yeah, I wanted to talk to you
about that. I was thinking

39:35.625 --> 39:37.792
we could move into my place.

39:37.792 --> 39:41.709
Your place with the crazy loud
neighbor and the dog that
doesn't stop barking?

39:41.709 --> 39:44.500
And you realize you live
right in the LAX flight path?

39:44.500 --> 39:46.083
We'll discuss this later.

39:46.083 --> 39:48.208
Because right now,
you owe me something.

39:49.625 --> 39:53.041
- Is Dave home?
- Why? Does it involve him?

39:53.041 --> 39:57.041
Unless you want our makeup sex
to be a makeup threesome, no.

39:59.583 --> 40:01.500
No, he's gone.
Let's go inside.

40:01.500 --> 40:05.333
- Should I wear my Bluetooth?
- Only your Bluetooth.

40:05.333 --> 40:07.583
- Hey, guess what we just hit?
- What?

40:07.583 --> 40:11.041
Seven weeks. We made it.

40:11.041 --> 40:12.417
[soft rock plays]

40:12.417 --> 40:17.041
♪ Don't you think it's time ♪

40:17.041 --> 40:21.667
♪ Time for moving on
Time for growing strong ♪

40:21.667 --> 40:23.542
- ♪ Time to leave... ♪
- [knocking]

40:23.542 --> 40:25.125
Coming!

40:27.583 --> 40:32.125
- Oh, are you Jamie?
- Yeah, the agency sent me over.

40:32.125 --> 40:36.542
- Oh, I don't think that...
- It's because I'm a guy, right?

40:36.542 --> 40:40.709
Don't rule me out
because of that. I've
got take out from Louise's,

40:40.709 --> 40:44.375
the second season of Lost on DVD
and a video monitor

40:44.375 --> 40:47.959
so we can watch that sweet
little princess of yours
in her crib.

40:47.959 --> 40:52.250
[laugh] I missed
the second season.

40:52.250 --> 40:55.417
Listen, the agency
can send you my references.

40:55.417 --> 40:59.834
I really think of myself
as a teacher, to get you
and your little one...

40:59.834 --> 41:02.250
- What's her name?
- Bella.

41:02.250 --> 41:06.125
To get you and Bella on your way
to a stress-free life.

41:06.959 --> 41:08.458
So where is this little Bella?

41:08.458 --> 41:10.208
Why don't you bring her on out

41:10.208 --> 41:12.834
so we can all get
to know each other a bit?

41:18.709 --> 41:20.375
[small laugh]

41:23.000 --> 41:24.625
Hey.

41:24.625 --> 41:27.458
Hey. I was worried
you weren't gonna make it.

41:27.458 --> 41:31.000
Yeah, sorry. It was a...
it was a late night.

41:31.000 --> 41:33.667
- Marjorie and I went
down to the beach.
- Alone?

41:33.667 --> 41:37.792
Well, nothing happened.
Almost nothing.

41:39.291 --> 41:42.959
She said she wants a second
chance. Wants to try again.

41:42.959 --> 41:44.166
You told her no, right?

41:47.542 --> 41:50.041
You're not gonna
leave Heather for Marjorie.

41:50.041 --> 41:52.375
Heather and I are
having a hard time.

41:52.375 --> 41:56.500
And we've been having
a hard time before Marjorie
ever showed up.

41:56.500 --> 41:57.917
So, what're you gonna do?

42:00.125 --> 42:02.375
Go for a run.

42:02.375 --> 42:03.917
[rock ballad plays]

42:03.917 --> 42:07.375
♪ Lost control again ♪♪
